            <title>[HIVE-27344] ORC RecordReaderImpl throws NPE when close() is called from the constructor</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HIVE-27344</link>
                <project id="12310843" key="HIVE">Hive</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;org.apache.hadoop.hive.ql.io.orc.RecordReaderImpl throws NullPointerException when the constructor of its super class org.apache.orc.impl.RecordReaderImpl calls this.close().&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;close() mutates the field &apos;batch&apos;, which is initialized after super class constructor is done. Therefore, we need a null check of field &apos;batch&apos; in close().&#160;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
